<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>Notion Journal Setup</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/styles.css" />
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class="container">
      <h1>Notion Journal Setup</h1>

      <div>
        <h3>📚 Step 1: Create a notebook</h3>
        <p>
          You can use any database-backed journal with this integration, for
          ease of use, we recommend you start with the default Notion "Journal"
          template:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Open Notion</li>
          <li>Click "New Page" in the top left corner</li>
          <li>Click "Templates"</li>
          <li>Search for "Journal"</li>
          <li>
            Click "Get Template" (It may take a while for the page to be
            created, wait a little bit for it to show up)
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3>🔗 Step 2: Add the integration</h3>
        <p>
          Authorize the integration to interact with whatever page you are going
          to journal in:
        </p>
        <div>
          <img src="/images/authorize.png" alt="Step 2 Image" width="300" />
        </div>
        <a
          href="https://api.notion.com/v1/oauth/authorize?client_id=f193a33f-4624-4f80-8245-94a31b138352&response_type=code&owner=user&redirect_uri=https%3A%2F%2Ftherabot-6f55c2bb2df3.herokuapp.com%2Fnotion%2Fregistration"
          >Authorize with Notion</a
        >
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3>📝 Step 3: Enter your information</h3>
        <p>
          After you authorize the Notion integration, you will be redirected to
          a user registration form. Fill out the user registration form to let
          us know how to read your journal database.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3>✍️ Step 4: Journal</h3>
        <p>
          Journal any way you want to! Feel free to change up the format of your
          pages and your database columns, as long as the id of your journal
          database stays the same, we can work with it!
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
